editorialNotes.standard: With its gorgeous photos and step-by-step instructions, this compilation of more than 15,000 recipes from The New York Times’ vaults belongs in every kitchen. We love how easy it is to save and search for recipes, and themed collections like “Easy Cakes,” “Beer Cocktails,” and “A Taste of New Orleans” are a mouthwatering delight. The app also features dozens of short instructional videos on topics like trussing chicken and julienning peppers—perfect for novice chefs eager to dive in and start cooking.

editorialNotes.standard: We all enjoy discovering new places and experiences but some of us don’t like to be surprised. If you’re one of those who prefers to research then Yelp is the right source for you. From restaurants and shops to night clubs and museums, check comments and ratings by fellow Yelpers and make sure you make the right choice.
editorialNotes.short: Eat before or after? Explore all of your restaurant options.

name: Too Good To Go: End Food Waste

editorialNotes.standard: We love shopping for low-cost Surprise Bags offered by restaurants, markets, specialty stores, and coffee shops each day. Fully prepped meals, baked goods, fresh produce—there’s a variety of options. Simply make a reservation and show up at the scheduled time.
editorialNotes.short: Don’t let your leftover food end up in the bin.

editorialNotes.tagline: Get a reservation in a few taps
editorialNotes.standard: Got a date to impress? Maybe you’re trying to celebrate your anniversary or meet up with a group of friends to grab something to eat. OpenTable makes it unbelievably easy to find the perfect place for the right occasion. Now save yourself some trouble by searching, exploring, and making a reservation all in one app.
editorialNotes.short: A guid to the most famous restaurants around you.

editorialNotes.standard: Even if you don’t consider yourself a cook, chances are you’ve been tempted to channel your inner chef after seeing one of the fun video recipes from Tasty that are all over the internet. These super-short, step-by-step cooking tutorials show how simple it can be to make everything from Cinnamon Roll French Toast to Mozzarella-Stuffed Meatballs to Apple Pie Cheesecake. The Tasty app puts more than 2,000 of these easy-to-digest videos on your iPhone or iPad.

editorialNotes.standard: Prepare delicious meals and maximize your grocery trips with this beautifully designed cooking app. Epicurious hosts thousands of searchable recipes across a wide range of categories, and you can easily save them to an organized recipe box or generate handy shopping lists. The more we use Epicurious, the more we love its timely content, mouthwatering photos, helpful customer ratings, and overall presentation.

editorialNotes.standard: This exceptional recipe manager makes every part of cooking easier. Organize recipes, create a meal calendar, and create grocery lists—then view instructions using the gorgeous cook mode. Adding new recipes is even easier: Import from URLs, scan from paper, view friends’ shared libraries, or subscribe to your favorite cooking blogs.

editorialNotes.standard: Sometimes, cooking or heading out to a restaurant just isn’t in the cards. Deliveroo makes those moments far more memorable by delivering meals from places that don’t normally do that. The quick, clean interface makes it super-easy to find nearby burgers, sushi—whatever’s calling your name—and then place an order. We particularly love how the real-time updates on the driver’s progress tell us exactly when you'll get to satisfy that appetite.
